    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A multivalent term referring to the solar year of 365 days counted in the xiuhpohualli (Nahua calendar) as well as a number of related concepts including the material and color of turquoise, herbacious plants or grasses, as well as asterisms such as comets and meteorites.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109721/GRI, FloCo terminology (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Un término polisémico que se refiere al año solar de 365 días contados en el xiuhpohualli (calendario nahua), así como una serie de conceptos relacionados, incluyendo el material y el color de la turquesa, las plantas o hierbas herbáceas, así como asterismos como cometas y meteoritos.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109721/GRI, FloCo terminology (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tlahtolli tlen quipiya miac queniuhcatzan hueli mocuamachilia huan quimanextia ce xihuitl solar tlen 365 tonatiuh, tlapohualli ipan xiuhpohualli (calendario nahua), quence miac conceptoz monehpanoah, calaqui tlamantli huan iixnezca chalchihuitl, xochimeh zo xihuimeh, quence xitlalmachiyotl, xitlalimeh huan tlixihuitl. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Eastern Huasteca Nahuatl</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
